My colleagues and I condemn the #BDS movement. We have sent a letter to the Office of Foreign Asset Control requesting an update on the federal government’s oversight of non-governmental organizations engaged in anti-Semitic hate against our allies in Israel.

I was honored to stand with @GovMattBevin, @kysenatepres, @BluegrassRabbi and others today for the ceremonial signing of SB 143, which prohibits Kentucky governmental agencies from using contractors who engage in boycotting Israel and our other trading partners. pic.twitter.com/zYY6xHJA5C

Mr. Bates received a Purple Heart and other medals for his willingness to protect and defend the freedoms we enjoy today, and he faced life with an unwavering faith in God and love of country.

Following several attempts to enlist before he became of legal age, Mr. Bates enlisted in the Marine Corps at the young age of 18. Just three days shy of his 19th birthday, Mr. Bates lost his left leg during an ambush on his unit.

I was humbled to speak on the House floor in honor of Winchester native and my friend, Roy Bates. A true hero and patriot, Bates passed away July 4, 2019. Watch my remarks here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k6jp1mi_Z74&t=4s …
